  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether Reiki energy healing affects anxiety and
      disease progression in patients with localized prostate cancer who are candidates for radical
      prostatectomy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      120 newly diagnosed prostate cancer patients will be randomized to one of 3 groups: Reiki,
      another touch therapy, or guided imagery. Subjects in the Reiki and touch therapy groups have
      8 sessions in the 4 weeks prior to their medical intervention. Those in the imagery group
      have one session prior to their medical intervention.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
